article.headline: Portland State 79, Bethune Cookman 62
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Anthony Washington scored 19 points and Tyler Hollist added 17 as Portland State defeated Bethune-Cookman College, 79-62, Monday. The visiting Vikings (1-1) jumped to a 6-0 lead and never trailed against the cold-shooting Wildcats. Jake Schroeder provided 14 points and Scott Morrison ten for Portland State, which beat the Wildcats by 20 points in last year's first-ever meeting between the two schools. Bethune-Cookman (1-3), which hit only 35.8 percent of its shots, put three players in double figures. Antonio Webb, despite making only four of 20 shots from the field, paced the Cats with 18 points. Kory Crumbley netted 11 points and Walter Murray ten. Portland State squandered its early lead when Murray and Crumbley brought the Cats even, 16-all, with 8:47 left in the first half. But the Washington-led Vikings pulled away the rest of the half, leading by ten, 34-24, at intermission. Washington's inside prowess propelled the Vikings in the second half, as they moved to a 17-point advantage, 52-35, with 12:10 to play. The host Cats used baskets by Crumbley and Webb to close the margin to eight points, 56-48, with 7:13 to go. But they could get no closer, as Portland State pulled away in the late stages.
